        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 3:58PM EDT until July 24 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Port Austin to near Elkton to near Unionville,
moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

These severe storms will be near...
Bad Axe, Sebewaing, Pigeon, Elkton, Kinde, and Owendale around 405
PM EDT.
Port Hope around 415 PM EDT.
Harbor Beach and Ubly around 425 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include
Redman, Parisville, Huron City, White Rock, Ivanhoe, Rapson,
Grindstone City, Bay Port, Ruth, and Pinnebog.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
